1
00:00:56,095 --> 00:00:58,973
FILING FOR LOVE

2
00:01:02,518 --> 00:01:05,980
EPISODE 12:
BECAUSE I LOVE YOU

3
00:01:47,813 --> 00:01:51,900
36 HOURS BEFORE M&amp;A

4
00:01:59,033 --> 00:02:00,117
Would you like a drink?

5
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:02,077
I don't think there's anything
left for us to talk about.

6
00:02:03,412 --> 00:02:04,496
No, wait.

7
00:02:06,373 --> 00:02:09,001
"Regret lingers more over the things
we never did than the things we did.

8
00:02:09,293 --> 00:02:12,713
And unrequited love lasts longer
than love that has faced its end."

9
00:02:13,756 --> 00:02:14,840
Do you remember saying that?

10
00:02:17,217 --> 00:02:19,345
"Attempt everything. Never stop.

11
00:02:19,678 --> 00:02:23,140
I will not let you end up regretting
the things you didn't do at Haemu."

12
00:02:24,933 --> 00:02:26,518
It's a quote
from your inaugural address

13
00:02:27,436 --> 00:02:29,521
that impressed me a great deal.

14
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:34,652
Keep your word.

15
00:02:35,527 --> 00:02:37,029
Don't make me regret anything.

16
00:02:46,705 --> 00:02:48,582
What a waste of good liquor.

17
00:02:50,668 --> 00:02:51,960
I quit drinking.

18
00:02:54,171 --> 00:02:55,547
I'll finish it, then.

19
00:03:05,933 --> 00:03:07,184
You have a good memory.

20
00:03:08,686 --> 00:03:10,312
Even I'd forgotten I'd said that.

21
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:13,816
I believed you were
a pretty decent leader.

22
00:03:15,150 --> 00:03:16,151
Back then, that is.

23
00:03:19,405 --> 00:03:20,656
That hits hard.

24
00:03:23,826 --> 00:03:25,202
I mean it.

25
00:03:25,536 --> 00:03:26,745
It was around the time

26
00:03:27,746 --> 00:03:29,581
I'd started to look down on Haemu.

27
00:03:30,416 --> 00:03:32,209
My superiors were fools

28
00:03:32,292 --> 00:03:34,002
and my coworkers were frustrating.

29
00:03:34,753 --> 00:03:36,338
The company seemed small.

30
00:03:42,386 --> 00:03:43,387
Yes.

31
00:03:43,762 --> 00:03:45,764
I was an arrogant punk.

32
00:03:46,765 --> 00:03:48,308
I thought my life

33
00:03:49,017 --> 00:03:52,479
was a straight highway
with no obstacles at all.

34
00:03:53,355 --> 00:03:55,065
That is, until I met Ms. Joo.

35
00:03:55,566 --> 00:03:59,570
In-a must've pulled the brakes
on your smooth-sailing life

36
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:01,822
when she demoted you
to handle PM cases.

37
00:04:02,072 --> 00:04:03,365
Reality hit hard.

38
00:04:04,074 --> 00:04:06,034
I thought,
"Why should I be doing this stuff?"

39
00:04:07,369 --> 00:04:09,037
Not long after that

40
00:04:09,413 --> 00:04:10,956
I started to feel ashamed.

41
00:04:12,666 --> 00:04:16,628
To me, Haemu was just a place
to do well, be acknowledged

42
00:04:16,837 --> 00:04:19,006
and prove myself to others.

43
00:04:21,216 --> 00:04:22,301
To someone else

44
00:04:23,260 --> 00:04:25,304
Haemu was a source of pride.

45
00:04:25,888 --> 00:04:28,265
- Please excuse me.
- It was a part of an enjoyable day

46
00:04:38,275 --> 00:04:41,403
and something they had to protect
at all costs.

47
00:04:41,862 --> 00:04:43,864
- Let's go!
- I realized that Haemu

48
00:04:43,947 --> 00:04:47,117
- Cheers!
- is where people come to work.

49
00:04:50,829 --> 00:04:52,998
I'd like you to think
of those very people.

50
00:04:54,082 --> 00:04:55,375
You wouldn't want

51
00:04:57,711 --> 00:04:59,463
to leave with regrets, would you?

52
00:05:28,659 --> 00:05:29,660
JEON JAE-YEOL

53
00:05:32,454 --> 00:05:33,539
Hello?

54
00:05:36,708 --> 00:05:37,709
What?

55
00:05:40,212 --> 00:05:41,922
Please excuse my intrusion.

56
00:05:52,432 --> 00:05:54,643
- Coffee?
- No, thanks.

57
00:05:54,726 --> 00:05:55,936
I'll get him out of here right away.

58
00:05:57,771 --> 00:05:59,898
Mr. Noh, get up this instant.

59
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:03,026
Hey, Ms. Joo, when did you get here?

60
00:06:03,110 --> 00:06:04,736
How much did you drink?

61
00:06:05,571 --> 00:06:08,574
- Are you the only one hungover?
- I guess so.

62
00:06:08,907 --> 00:06:11,410
I don't think I drank that much,
but I must've dozed off.

63
00:06:14,580 --> 00:06:15,998
What's this?

64
00:06:18,375 --> 00:06:19,835
Did you cover me up with this?

65
00:06:20,669 --> 00:06:22,588
How sweet of you.

66
00:06:23,839 --> 00:06:25,632
That's enough nonsense.

67
00:06:26,508 --> 00:06:27,551
Let's get to the point.

68
00:06:29,136 --> 00:06:30,137
What now?

69
00:06:30,637 --> 00:06:32,389
What do you need me to do?

70
00:06:34,141 --> 00:06:36,435
Did you change your mind?

71
00:06:40,689 --> 00:06:42,858
Mr. Noh tells a pretty good story.

72
00:06:51,658 --> 00:06:52,993
24 HOURS BEFORE M&amp;A

73
00:06:53,076 --> 00:06:55,913
The main subsidiaries
will be sold off tomorrow.

74
00:06:55,996 --> 00:06:58,957
So you want to hold a board meeting
and dismiss Sung-yeol before then?

75
00:06:59,041 --> 00:07:00,292
Yes, that's right.

76
00:07:00,375 --> 00:07:03,503
Out of the directors,
Director Woo is most against the M&amp;A.

77
00:07:04,004 --> 00:07:07,424
Meet Director Woo
and persuade him to call the meeting.

78
00:07:07,507 --> 00:07:09,927
I'm not saying
I'll return to management.

79
00:07:10,218 --> 00:07:11,970
I want to break from tradition

80
00:07:12,054 --> 00:07:13,972
and hire a management specialist.

81
00:07:14,765 --> 00:07:18,644
Do you think you can
achieve that on your own?

82
00:07:18,894 --> 00:07:20,395
Some employees are on my side.

83
00:07:20,479 --> 00:07:22,230
There will be a change
from the roots up.

84
00:07:24,024 --> 00:07:25,943
I won't be leading from the front.

85
00:07:26,610 --> 00:07:28,111
I'll be supporting from behind.

86
00:07:28,487 --> 00:07:30,489
When Director Woo calls the board

87
00:07:30,614 --> 00:07:33,951
we must persuade a majority
of the other directors to attend.

88
00:07:34,034 --> 00:07:35,994
This is the only way to stop the M&amp;A.

89
00:07:36,078 --> 00:07:37,663
We can't manage on our own.

90
00:07:38,121 --> 00:07:39,790
I'll ask Team Three for their help.

91
00:07:42,876 --> 00:07:44,711
That's Director Yoon over there.

92
00:07:44,795 --> 00:07:46,421
Yes. I see him.

93
00:07:48,674 --> 00:07:50,926
AIRPORT TERMINAL

94
00:08:02,062 --> 00:08:04,940
- Oh, hello, sir.
- What are you doing?

95
00:08:05,023 --> 00:08:06,274
You can't leave.

96
00:08:15,117 --> 00:08:16,368
- Please help.
- Oh, gosh.

97
00:08:19,162 --> 00:08:20,163
JEON SUNG-YEOL

98
00:08:20,247 --> 00:08:21,373
An emergency board meeting?

99
00:08:24,876 --> 00:08:27,629
So Jae-yeol has started to move.

100
00:08:28,839 --> 00:08:30,632
It's fine as long as the majority
doesn't attend.

101
00:08:31,633 --> 00:08:34,886
Director Park and Director Jeong
won't be interested anyway.

102
00:08:35,929 --> 00:08:38,140
- Call Director Ha.
- Yes, sir.

103
00:08:39,016 --> 00:08:40,100
Oh, one more thing.

104
00:08:40,642 --> 00:08:44,104
Be sure the deal
to sell HM Trans is on track.

105
00:08:44,354 --> 00:08:45,897
Sure, I understand.

106
00:08:49,234 --> 00:08:51,820
3 HOURS BEFORE M&amp;A

107
00:08:56,408 --> 00:08:57,534
How did it go?

108
00:08:57,743 --> 00:08:59,494
Director Ha didn't come
to the meeting place.

109
00:08:59,578 --> 00:09:00,871
He won't take our calls, either.

110
00:09:01,705 --> 00:09:04,416
I think he sided with Jeon Sung-yeol.

111
00:09:10,088 --> 00:09:11,673
They'll be signing the deal soon.

112
00:09:19,347 --> 00:09:20,766
President Jeon.

113
00:09:21,933 --> 00:09:24,019
He's still a registered board member.

114
00:09:24,978 --> 00:09:26,271
Forget it.

115
00:09:26,938 --> 00:09:28,732
I have no reason to do that.

116
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:31,693
The game is over already.

117
00:09:32,861 --> 00:09:36,198
You lost to him completely
at the shareholders' meeting.

118
00:09:37,199 --> 00:09:38,742
I don't want to side with a loser.

119
00:09:40,619 --> 00:09:41,870
Father.

120
00:09:42,370 --> 00:09:44,122
What did I fight for all this time?

121
00:09:45,457 --> 00:09:48,919
The reason I spent my entire life
trying to win and earn recognition

122
00:09:49,419 --> 00:09:51,713
in the fight you set up for me

123
00:09:53,131 --> 00:09:56,093
is that I understood
the purpose of that fight.

124
00:09:56,718 --> 00:09:59,137
"The strongest shall survive
to lead Haemu."

125
00:10:00,263 --> 00:10:01,681
I believed that, too.

126
00:10:03,058 --> 00:10:05,185
But look at Haemu now.

127
00:10:05,268 --> 00:10:07,729
Look at the company
you tried to protect.

128
00:10:09,940 --> 00:10:11,274
Is this how you want it to be?

129
00:10:14,152 --> 00:10:15,779
You had once told me

130
00:10:16,196 --> 00:10:20,283
that protecting something
means discarding everything else.

131
00:10:24,204 --> 00:10:26,373
I came here to protect Haemu.

132
00:10:26,706 --> 00:10:29,876
I gave up on an ordinary life,
my pathetic ego

133
00:10:32,921 --> 00:10:36,133
and my hatred and resentment for you.

134
00:10:38,718 --> 00:10:41,054
So, will you please put aside
your disappointment in me

135
00:10:42,430 --> 00:10:44,099
for a short while?

136
00:10:46,518 --> 00:10:47,811
For Haemu's sake.

137
00:10:49,479 --> 00:10:52,232
MARCH 11, 2026
SIGNED BY JEON SUNG-YEOL

138
00:11:15,630 --> 00:11:17,424
What do you think you're doing?

139
00:11:17,507 --> 00:11:19,801
The deal you just signed is invalid.

140
00:11:20,552 --> 00:11:22,888
The board dismissed VP Jeon Sung-yeol

141
00:11:23,847 --> 00:11:26,183
and he has no right to sign the deal.

142
00:11:26,474 --> 00:11:28,602
What stupid prank is this?

143
00:11:29,019 --> 00:11:31,271
We already signed
and exchanged the papers.

144
00:11:32,397 --> 00:11:35,275
The board passed the resolution
to remove you

145
00:11:35,358 --> 00:11:37,319
at 2:25 p.m. on March 11, 2026.

146
00:11:38,278 --> 00:11:40,322
According to Article 17
of Haemu's company charter

147
00:11:40,739 --> 00:11:42,532
you lose all authority

148
00:11:43,742 --> 00:11:45,702
the moment you are dismissed.

149
00:11:49,998 --> 00:11:51,374
That's impossible.

150
00:11:52,292 --> 00:11:53,418
VOTING RESULTS
TO DISMISS VP JEON SUNG-YEOL

151
00:11:53,501 --> 00:11:56,171
What is this? How come...

152
00:11:57,088 --> 00:12:00,258
- Ms. Park, where is Director Ha?
- He's at his residence.

153
00:12:01,218 --> 00:12:02,427
Then who else signed this?

154
00:12:05,639 --> 00:12:06,932
Father?

155
00:12:07,015 --> 00:12:08,099
DISMISSAL OF AN EXECUTIVE

156
00:12:08,183 --> 00:12:09,517
PRESIDENT JEON MOO-TAE

157
00:12:09,601 --> 00:12:11,561
Why would Father sign...

158
00:12:11,645 --> 00:12:13,563
What on earth is going on?

159
00:12:13,647 --> 00:12:16,858
We informed your company
as soon as the resolution passed.

160
00:12:16,942 --> 00:12:18,777
I'm sure you don't want to face
the legal risk

161
00:12:18,860 --> 00:12:20,570
of signing a deal
with an unauthorized proxy.

162
00:12:21,404 --> 00:12:24,991
The emergency board meeting
adhered to all laws and charters.

163
00:12:25,825 --> 00:12:27,744
If you still want to challenge
its validity

164
00:12:28,954 --> 00:12:30,413
we'll meet you in court.

165
00:12:47,681 --> 00:12:49,099
When did you set this up?

166
00:12:50,475 --> 00:12:52,602
You acted like
you didn't care or want anything.

167
00:12:53,520 --> 00:12:55,230
Were you hiding your talons
all this time?

168
00:12:57,524 --> 00:12:59,109
I'm not here to steal what's yours.

169
00:13:00,860 --> 00:13:02,904
I'm here
so I can leave without regret.

170
00:13:35,478 --> 00:13:37,022
How typical of him
to leave behind a mess.

171
00:13:37,355 --> 00:13:41,443
I think he destroyed the files
that could pose a problem later on.

172
00:13:45,280 --> 00:13:46,823
I kept backup copies.

173
00:13:50,410 --> 00:13:51,786
You're still very meticulous.

174
00:13:53,038 --> 00:13:54,497
That's how you took me down.

175
00:13:58,001 --> 00:13:59,461
Why did you change your mind?

176
00:14:01,254 --> 00:14:02,422
I realized

177
00:14:04,716 --> 00:14:07,344
I wasn't as bad a person
as I thought.

178
00:14:40,335 --> 00:14:42,962
Man, it was like
a scene from a movie.

179
00:14:43,046 --> 00:14:45,006
It was more film-like than a film.

180
00:14:45,382 --> 00:14:47,550
Guess how many times Hae-young and I
drove around the golf club.

181
00:14:47,634 --> 00:14:49,761
You all had a partner, at least.

182
00:14:49,844 --> 00:14:52,889
I went on my own
to Director Min's home.

183
00:14:53,223 --> 00:14:56,393
You know he has the worst temper
out of all the directors, don't you?

184
00:14:56,476 --> 00:14:58,853
- Come on.
- His temper isn't the worst.

185
00:14:58,937 --> 00:15:01,564
We had to deal with Director Yoon
who put up a fight.

186
00:15:01,648 --> 00:15:04,359
- Right?
- Right, and we subdued him.

187
00:15:05,485 --> 00:15:07,779
We almost had to board a plane.

188
00:15:14,744 --> 00:15:16,371
Great work today.

189
00:15:17,872 --> 00:15:19,707
I owe it to them for their help.

190
00:15:20,166 --> 00:15:23,086
We couldn't have done it without you.

191
00:15:24,462 --> 00:15:25,797
Good job.

192
00:15:28,758 --> 00:15:30,468
Is Jae-yeol joining us for dinner?

193
00:15:31,886 --> 00:15:33,888
Why don't you give him a call?

194
00:15:33,972 --> 00:15:35,849
You two met up just fine without me.

195
00:15:37,308 --> 00:15:38,935
It is a shame.

196
00:15:39,519 --> 00:15:42,063
If we hadn't met
as your ex and current boyfriend

197
00:15:42,147 --> 00:15:43,815
we could've been really close.

198
00:15:46,192 --> 00:15:47,402
I mean it.

199
00:15:48,111 --> 00:15:50,238
I see why you dated him.

200
00:15:50,530 --> 00:15:51,614
He's pretty cool.

201
00:15:53,074 --> 00:15:55,285
You're cool, too.
You don't seem jealous.

202
00:15:56,369 --> 00:15:57,662
Why would I be jealous?

203
00:15:59,372 --> 00:16:01,458
I'm the one you're with now.

204
00:16:03,209 --> 00:16:05,753
Who cares? They all know.

205
00:16:05,837 --> 00:16:07,672
Mr. Noh... Hey, what's going on?

206
00:16:07,922 --> 00:16:09,466
Are you two holding hands?

207
00:16:09,549 --> 00:16:11,759
Are you holding hands
in the open now?

208
00:16:11,843 --> 00:16:14,429
Why don't you two treat us all?

209
00:16:17,390 --> 00:16:19,976
Yes, we're holding hands,
and we'll treat you all!

210
00:16:20,310 --> 00:16:22,312
- Yes!
- Let's eat!

211
00:16:23,771 --> 00:16:25,982
- How about beef?
- Sounds good.

212
00:16:27,901 --> 00:16:29,444
Beef is expensive.

213
00:16:30,111 --> 00:16:32,071
- No beef?
- Come on...

214
00:16:42,665 --> 00:16:46,628
1 YEAR LATER

215
00:16:46,711 --> 00:16:48,671
HEAD OF SALES DIVISION, LIM HYEOK-JUN

216
00:17:00,517 --> 00:17:02,060
The target's on the move.

217
00:17:02,477 --> 00:17:03,770
Oh, over.

218
00:17:16,282 --> 00:17:18,034
Target's on the move. Stand by, Tail.

219
00:17:49,148 --> 00:17:51,359
Target found. I'm tailing him.

220
00:17:56,906 --> 00:17:58,157
Oh, shoot.

221
00:18:03,162 --> 00:18:04,414
Let's go.

222
00:18:44,787 --> 00:18:47,332
We were right on the money.

223
00:18:48,458 --> 00:18:49,584
You're up.

224
00:18:51,753 --> 00:18:53,087
Be careful.

225
00:18:58,676 --> 00:18:59,844
We're moving in.

226
00:19:00,928 --> 00:19:01,929
Go on.

227
00:19:05,350 --> 00:19:06,976
Are we really going in?

228
00:19:09,312 --> 00:19:10,313
Hey.

229
00:19:11,773 --> 00:19:12,982
Step aside.

230
00:19:14,734 --> 00:19:15,985
Director Lim!

231
00:19:19,822 --> 00:19:21,074
Stop what you're doing.

232
00:19:21,157 --> 00:19:22,617
We're from the Audit Team.

233
00:19:23,993 --> 00:19:26,204
What are you doing here?

234
00:19:26,621 --> 00:19:28,206
You said you were out on business.

235
00:19:28,289 --> 00:19:29,957
What are you selling here?

236
00:19:31,751 --> 00:19:35,254
I wanted to spruce up
before meeting my sales contacts.

237
00:19:35,713 --> 00:19:36,756
I'm trying to look clean.

238
00:19:37,298 --> 00:19:40,927
Coming to a bathhouse
to spruce up during work hours

239
00:19:41,302 --> 00:19:43,179
is a dereliction of duty.

240
00:19:43,554 --> 00:19:45,932
Even more so if you do it every day.

241
00:19:54,565 --> 00:19:56,359
Rookie, get a hold of yourself.

242
00:19:56,693 --> 00:19:59,445
I told you to move in.
Why did you hesitate?

243
00:19:59,737 --> 00:20:01,948
What if we missed our opportunity?

244
00:20:02,573 --> 00:20:04,283
Nothing that bad would've happened.

245
00:20:05,243 --> 00:20:07,912
- Pardon?
- That's the truth.

246
00:20:07,995 --> 00:20:10,373
And I don't see
why we must do this anyway.

247
00:20:10,707 --> 00:20:14,085
I studied in the US and did well
on Haemu's entrance exam.

248
00:20:14,836 --> 00:20:16,045
I don't get

249
00:20:16,587 --> 00:20:19,215
why I should do this stuff.

250
00:20:24,637 --> 00:20:25,763
This "stuff"?

251
00:20:27,932 --> 00:20:28,975
Who do you think you are?

252
00:20:29,058 --> 00:20:30,935
Do you have superpowers? Can you fly?

253
00:20:31,018 --> 00:20:33,020
Can you teleport or do a palm blast?

254
00:20:37,108 --> 00:20:39,360
No rookie has the right
to decide what to do or not.

255
00:20:41,070 --> 00:20:42,488
Don't look down on what we do.

256
00:20:43,364 --> 00:20:47,660
Everything the Audit Team does
is equally important.

257
00:20:49,787 --> 00:20:52,248
Don't you think that sounds familiar?

258
00:20:52,331 --> 00:20:53,750
- Yes.
- Right?

259
00:20:53,833 --> 00:20:56,252
It's all good.
You caught him red-handed.

260
00:20:56,335 --> 00:20:57,920
You did well.

261
00:20:58,254 --> 00:21:01,424
- Don't neglect your health.
- Thank you.

262
00:21:02,467 --> 00:21:04,302
Here you go, Mr. Noh.

263
00:21:07,430 --> 00:21:08,514
And our rookie.

264
00:21:09,223 --> 00:21:10,349
Thank you.

265
00:21:13,019 --> 00:21:14,020
You smiled?

266
00:21:18,691 --> 00:21:19,859
Did you just smile?

267
00:21:23,821 --> 00:21:26,991
I like that. You should smile.
Smiling brings fortune.

268
00:21:28,659 --> 00:21:29,827
Thank you.

269
00:21:31,913 --> 00:21:33,289
Here's some for Team Two.

270
00:21:33,623 --> 00:21:35,458
Stay healthy.

271
00:21:36,334 --> 00:21:38,002
Am I the only one who finds this odd?

272
00:21:38,085 --> 00:21:40,213
There's no middle ground.
She's so extreme.

273
00:21:40,296 --> 00:21:42,715
It feels like they're starting
to swap personalities.

274
00:21:43,257 --> 00:21:45,551
They say you grow alike
with the one you love.

275
00:21:59,106 --> 00:22:01,984
How is life abroad?
Is your mother well?

276
00:22:02,401 --> 00:22:03,945
I like the peace and quiet.

277
00:22:04,278 --> 00:22:05,655
My mother settled in right away.

278
00:22:06,739 --> 00:22:09,075
I flew in to handle something else.

279
00:22:09,659 --> 00:22:11,577
I didn't think I'd run into you here.

280
00:22:13,496 --> 00:22:16,249
You wouldn't take my calls,
so I had to get creative.

281
00:22:23,840 --> 00:22:26,425
We're developing
a new medication to target

282
00:22:26,509 --> 00:22:28,052
treatment-resistant mental illnesses.

283
00:22:28,469 --> 00:22:31,138
The roadmap takes into account
possible medical clusters.

284
00:22:31,556 --> 00:22:33,266
We've already signed
R&amp;D partnership MOUs

285
00:22:33,349 --> 00:22:35,977
with several
major university hospitals in Korea.

286
00:22:36,644 --> 00:22:38,813
What we need now are investments.

287
00:22:39,647 --> 00:22:42,692
But this is a large-scale project
beyond the foundation's capacity.

288
00:22:44,235 --> 00:22:46,445
We desperately need
your connections and wisdom.

289
00:22:47,405 --> 00:22:49,031
JEI MEDICAL FOUNDATION
CNS RESEARCH CENTER

290
00:22:53,744 --> 00:22:55,329
Jei Medical Foundation

291
00:22:56,414 --> 00:22:58,624
went through a rough patch
because of me.

292
00:22:59,709 --> 00:23:03,337
Won't my involvement
harm their image?

293
00:23:03,546 --> 00:23:08,509
Everyone knows how devoted you were
to helping your mother.

294
00:23:08,885 --> 00:23:11,679
What motive could be
stronger than sincerity?

295
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:26,360
It looks delicious.

296
00:23:30,031 --> 00:23:31,741
Mr. Noh Ki-jun.

297
00:23:32,033 --> 00:23:34,577
Why are you so hard on the rookie?

298
00:23:35,286 --> 00:23:36,954
He was close to bursting into tears.

299
00:23:37,038 --> 00:23:40,708
Come on. Since when did you become
such a caring boss?

300
00:23:40,791 --> 00:23:42,293
Think of how you treated me.

301
00:23:43,210 --> 00:23:45,922
And that is how you become
a mean-spirited superior.

302
00:23:52,845 --> 00:23:54,472
It's so good.

303
00:23:55,431 --> 00:23:56,974
Doesn't it look easy to make?

304
00:23:57,058 --> 00:23:58,100
I should give it a try.

305
00:24:01,437 --> 00:24:05,483
You seem oddly upbeat today.

306
00:24:11,530 --> 00:24:12,615
Well...

307
00:24:13,908 --> 00:24:16,410
I have something to tell you.
Hang on.

308
00:24:20,164 --> 00:24:21,165
So...

309
00:24:21,916 --> 00:24:23,334
I bought a place.

310
00:24:23,584 --> 00:24:24,919
- A house?
- Yes.

311
00:24:25,002 --> 00:24:27,254
A short-term rental? No.
A long-term rental? No.

312
00:24:27,338 --> 00:24:28,714
It's completely my own.

313
00:24:29,173 --> 00:24:32,093
The building's a bit old,
but it's perfect for one person

314
00:24:32,176 --> 00:24:33,636
and it's close to where you live.

315
00:24:33,719 --> 00:24:35,137
Isn't that just great?

316
00:24:35,221 --> 00:24:36,722
Yes, but...

317
00:24:37,014 --> 00:24:38,349
did you want to move?

318
00:24:38,432 --> 00:24:42,019
My landlord suddenly asked me to move
so he could move in.

319
00:24:42,103 --> 00:24:43,729
I had to rush to find a new place

320
00:24:43,813 --> 00:24:45,856
and I came across
an apartment for sale.

321
00:24:45,940 --> 00:24:48,150
I decided to take the plunge
and buy a place outright.

322
00:24:59,829 --> 00:25:01,038
The reason

323
00:25:01,122 --> 00:25:04,125
I didn't tell you is that
I didn't want to cause you trouble.

324
00:25:04,208 --> 00:25:05,960
- You're already busy with work.
- You know

325
00:25:06,043 --> 00:25:09,213
we see each other at work every day
and eat dinner afterward.

326
00:25:09,296 --> 00:25:11,173
We even go on dates on weekends.

327
00:25:11,257 --> 00:25:14,760
We tell each other everything,
yet you had no time to tell me that?

328
00:25:15,761 --> 00:25:18,389
What I'm saying is,
I didn't tell you.

329
00:25:19,724 --> 00:25:21,642
I don't like it
when you worry about me.

330
00:25:23,477 --> 00:25:25,312
Sure. I know what you're like.

331
00:25:26,272 --> 00:25:29,567
I'll try to understand that
you have issues you don't tell me.

332
00:25:30,026 --> 00:25:31,193
That's what you're like.

333
00:25:33,195 --> 00:25:35,906
I'm sorry. Don't be angry, okay?

334
00:25:35,990 --> 00:25:37,992
So you went and bought an apartment?

335
00:25:38,659 --> 00:25:40,202
Perfect for one person?

336
00:25:41,412 --> 00:25:42,621
That means

337
00:25:43,372 --> 00:25:45,291
you have no intentions
of living with me.

338
00:25:47,084 --> 00:25:48,085
Well...

339
00:25:50,629 --> 00:25:52,798
We practically live together
right now.

340
00:25:52,882 --> 00:25:56,510
- You come over or I come to yours.
- Exactly. We do that now.

341
00:25:56,594 --> 00:25:58,387
Don't you want to move in?

342
00:25:59,889 --> 00:26:01,682
Are you saying
we should live together?

343
00:26:05,394 --> 00:26:06,479
Wait...

344
00:26:07,063 --> 00:26:08,064
A marriage?

345
00:26:10,483 --> 00:26:12,651
- Are you insane?
- Excuse me? "Insane"?

346
00:26:12,735 --> 00:26:14,195
Marriage?

347
00:26:14,278 --> 00:26:16,947
- Why would I marry?
- Why wouldn't you?

348
00:26:18,074 --> 00:26:19,075
It's just...

349
00:26:19,450 --> 00:26:21,410
I won't. I don't do marriages.

350
00:26:22,203 --> 00:26:24,246
Not even with me?

351
00:26:25,664 --> 00:26:26,791
That's...

352
00:26:28,876 --> 00:26:30,336
I never thought about it.

353
00:26:33,464 --> 00:26:34,799
Then start thinking about it.

354
00:26:35,341 --> 00:26:36,884
What? But...

355
00:26:38,135 --> 00:26:41,180
That's too one-sided on your part.
It's a huge decision.

356
00:26:43,432 --> 00:26:45,142
You called me a variable.

357
00:26:45,810 --> 00:26:48,020
An unexpected variable
that entered your life.

358
00:26:50,523 --> 00:26:51,941
I don't want to be that anymore.

359
00:26:53,359 --> 00:26:54,860
I want us to talk and discuss

360
00:26:54,944 --> 00:26:57,780
our plans ten or 20 years later
until the day we die.

361
00:26:59,156 --> 00:27:00,825
I want to plan everything with you.

362
00:27:01,659 --> 00:27:05,371
I want to be a constant in your life.

363
00:27:06,372 --> 00:27:07,540
Ki-jun.

364
00:27:08,415 --> 00:27:11,377
- You have your own life.
- It can be our life.

365
00:27:12,253 --> 00:27:13,671
A life we share together.

366
00:27:38,571 --> 00:27:39,655
CONCLUSION AND EXPECTED BENEFITS

367
00:27:39,738 --> 00:27:42,575
Separating the Audit Team isn't about
changing the organizational chart.

368
00:27:43,075 --> 00:27:45,494
We want to be independent
of the managerial executives

369
00:27:45,578 --> 00:27:48,205
to avoid being influenced
by internal politics.

370
00:27:48,289 --> 00:27:51,125
It's a structural shift
that allows us to stand alone.

371
00:27:51,709 --> 00:27:53,544
There will be
many initial difficulties

372
00:27:53,627 --> 00:27:56,881
but it can become a reality
if the company and we are determined.

373
00:27:56,964 --> 00:28:00,134
I believe it's a system
that must be implemented.

374
00:28:01,218 --> 00:28:03,429
That concludes my explanation
of the roadmap.

375
00:28:07,099 --> 00:28:08,559
You have no questions, do you?

376
00:28:08,642 --> 00:28:11,478
You must be very busy.
You can return upstairs...

377
00:28:15,441 --> 00:28:16,525
Mr. Noh?

378
00:28:18,444 --> 00:28:20,654
What happens when we're separated
from other departments

379
00:28:20,863 --> 00:28:24,074
preventing us from accessing data
due to security risks?

380
00:28:24,700 --> 00:28:27,077
Won't we have to beg others
for information?

381
00:28:29,038 --> 00:28:31,415
The board approved this move.

382
00:28:31,498 --> 00:28:34,460
We're guaranteed
unlimited access to all data

383
00:28:34,543 --> 00:28:37,838
and Head of IT will be
held accountable if they refuse.

384
00:28:37,922 --> 00:28:39,173
What about the budget?

385
00:28:39,256 --> 00:28:41,717
We'll lose our customary speed
if we can't sign anything

386
00:28:41,800 --> 00:28:42,927
without the board's approval.

387
00:28:43,010 --> 00:28:44,929
We only need approval
for our annual budget.

388
00:28:45,012 --> 00:28:47,514
The Head of Audit
will allocate the necessary funds.

389
00:28:47,598 --> 00:28:51,268
They're all ideals
that look good on paper.

390
00:28:51,352 --> 00:28:53,312
What if we try to break free
from management

391
00:28:53,395 --> 00:28:55,898
only to have to tiptoe around
all the other departments?

392
00:28:59,443 --> 00:29:00,694
It doesn't look like

393
00:29:01,195 --> 00:29:03,322
you tiptoe around anyone at work.

394
00:29:05,324 --> 00:29:06,951
Am I wrong?

395
00:29:19,588 --> 00:29:21,257
That was intense.

396
00:29:21,340 --> 00:29:22,800
I almost wet myself.

397
00:29:23,217 --> 00:29:24,301
Me, too.

398
00:29:24,385 --> 00:29:27,888
Mr. Noh challenged Ms. Joo
a bit too much in public.

399
00:29:27,972 --> 00:29:29,556
I see why he would, though.

400
00:29:29,640 --> 00:29:31,100
Ms. Joo was too harsh on him.

401
00:29:31,517 --> 00:29:33,602
Everyone pretends to have forgotten,
but I remember.

402
00:29:33,686 --> 00:29:38,440
Ms. Joo went to the reporters
and told them that she used Ki-jun

403
00:29:38,524 --> 00:29:40,401
then came back
without so much as an apology.

404
00:29:40,484 --> 00:29:42,152
Mr. Noh must hate it.

405
00:29:42,861 --> 00:29:45,114
Could there still be

406
00:29:45,239 --> 00:29:47,992
something between them?

407
00:29:48,409 --> 00:29:51,954
- Like what?
- Forget about her using him.

408
00:29:52,037 --> 00:29:53,580
They had something going on.

409
00:29:54,373 --> 00:29:57,209
- Yes.
- And lashing out like that here...

410
00:29:57,293 --> 00:29:59,920
- It's not like that!
- Have you heard, Mr. Sung?

411
00:30:00,671 --> 00:30:02,923
Mr. Oh from Planning
and Ms. Seon from Finance

412
00:30:03,007 --> 00:30:05,009
are getting married.
Isn't that crazy?

413
00:30:07,845 --> 00:30:09,638
Yes, I heard about that.

414
00:30:10,180 --> 00:30:12,391
- He must have an idea.
- Yes, right.

415
00:30:12,474 --> 00:30:14,184
- You can...
- Team One.

416
00:30:14,268 --> 00:30:17,354
The expense... Where is
this quarter's expense report?

417
00:30:19,106 --> 00:30:20,274
You want that now?

418
00:30:23,777 --> 00:30:25,279
Something's fishy.

419
00:30:29,033 --> 00:30:30,159
Wait a minute.

420
00:30:32,786 --> 00:30:35,622
You're all acting suspiciously.

421
00:30:35,706 --> 00:30:37,666
Are you into stocks?
I have some good info.

422
00:30:37,750 --> 00:30:39,460
- For your ears only.
- For real?

423
00:30:40,252 --> 00:30:43,964
I'm hurt. You're hiding something
from us, aren't you?

424
00:30:44,048 --> 00:30:45,049
How dare you!

425
00:31:00,773 --> 00:31:02,316
- Is he okay?
- Sorry.

426
00:31:02,691 --> 00:31:04,610
I'm sorry, Min-su.

427
00:31:04,693 --> 00:31:06,070
Why did he slap him?

428
00:31:07,696 --> 00:31:10,366
Why did you slap him,
White Blood Cell?

429
00:31:13,285 --> 00:31:14,787
- Hello.
- You're here.

430
00:31:15,496 --> 00:31:16,622
Come and sit down.

431
00:31:18,624 --> 00:31:19,875
Hurry and take a seat.

432
00:31:46,777 --> 00:31:49,905
We get the chills
when you act like that at work.

433
00:31:50,739 --> 00:31:53,033
We all tiptoe around you.

434
00:31:53,784 --> 00:31:56,120
In-house couples get caught

435
00:31:56,203 --> 00:31:58,497
because they can't hide
how they feel.

436
00:31:58,705 --> 00:32:01,959
Even if we go to such lengths
to cover up for you

437
00:32:02,042 --> 00:32:03,961
you're making things so obvious.

438
00:32:04,628 --> 00:32:07,798
Why don't you two
fill each other's glasses?

439
00:32:21,812 --> 00:32:23,605
Now repeat after me.

440
00:32:24,189 --> 00:32:25,607
"I am sorry."

441
00:32:26,483 --> 00:32:28,694
It may feel weird and embarrassing

442
00:32:28,777 --> 00:32:31,738
but this is what
I make my kids do after they fight.

443
00:32:31,822 --> 00:32:34,408
Give it a go. "I am sorry."

444
00:32:36,743 --> 00:32:38,036
- I'm sorry.
- I'm sorry.

445
00:32:38,912 --> 00:32:40,038
"I love you."

446
00:32:43,250 --> 00:32:44,710
- I love you.
- I love you.

447
00:32:45,085 --> 00:32:46,753
Now clink glasses.

448
00:32:53,469 --> 00:32:55,387
- Well done.
- Bravo.

449
00:32:55,471 --> 00:32:57,598
- It's all done.
- Congratulations.

450
00:32:58,265 --> 00:33:01,685
I guess it was
a serious fight this time.

451
00:33:02,769 --> 00:33:03,812
What was it about?

452
00:33:17,034 --> 00:33:19,828
Of course, you must marry
if you want to be happy.

453
00:33:19,912 --> 00:33:23,707
You work like crazy all day long
just to return to an empty home.

454
00:33:24,082 --> 00:33:26,168
How is that a happy life? Am I wrong?

455
00:33:26,251 --> 00:33:28,212
That's the best moment of my day.

456
00:33:28,295 --> 00:33:30,506
I suffer all day long
with work and people

457
00:33:30,589 --> 00:33:32,966
but thinking of going home
to even more people

458
00:33:33,467 --> 00:33:34,718
sounds horrible.

459
00:33:34,968 --> 00:33:37,596
Ms. Yoon. Do we give you a hard time?

460
00:33:37,679 --> 00:33:39,264
She's saying

461
00:33:39,348 --> 00:33:42,976
we all find happiness
in different things.

462
00:33:43,310 --> 00:33:46,647
I've been dating my boyfriend
for over ten years

463
00:33:46,730 --> 00:33:48,232
but I don't want to marry him.

464
00:33:48,524 --> 00:33:50,234
He doesn't have a stable income

465
00:33:50,317 --> 00:33:53,111
and he travels to find inspiration
out of the blue.

466
00:33:53,195 --> 00:33:55,405
How could I ask
a free spirit like him

467
00:33:55,489 --> 00:33:57,991
to buy an apartment
and have kids with me?

468
00:33:58,075 --> 00:34:02,079
Yes, but if you're in love,
you want to be together

469
00:34:02,162 --> 00:34:03,747
and plan a future.

470
00:34:03,830 --> 00:34:06,458
Doesn't that make you want to marry?

471
00:34:06,542 --> 00:34:07,960
- That's exactly it.
- Yes.

472
00:34:08,335 --> 00:34:11,296
White Blood Cell,
if that's what you think marriage is

473
00:34:11,380 --> 00:34:12,631
don't ever get married.

474
00:34:12,714 --> 00:34:14,550
Marriage is the real deal.

475
00:34:15,175 --> 00:34:17,970
Did your dream come true
when you got a girlfriend in college?

476
00:34:18,637 --> 00:34:19,805
No, right?

477
00:34:19,888 --> 00:34:22,057
Did finding a job
make you a cool adult?

478
00:34:22,140 --> 00:34:24,977
It didn't.
Life is still gloomy and hard.

479
00:34:25,060 --> 00:34:26,228
Marriage is the same.

480
00:34:26,311 --> 00:34:28,855
Does that mean you shouldn't go
to college or get a job?

481
00:34:28,939 --> 00:34:32,359
You speak so negatively,
but you're happily married.

482
00:34:32,609 --> 00:34:34,820
You can build a life together.

483
00:34:35,279 --> 00:34:37,197
Marriage is different
from college or work.

484
00:34:37,281 --> 00:34:39,199
Those are choices you make yourself.

485
00:34:39,283 --> 00:34:41,368
Marriage is a compromise
between two people.

486
00:34:41,451 --> 00:34:43,245
- It's double the risk.
- Yes.

487
00:34:44,079 --> 00:34:46,373
"Risk"? Do you think
marriage is an audit case

488
00:34:46,456 --> 00:34:48,750
where you calculate every risk?

489
00:34:48,834 --> 00:34:52,796
Of course. My life is at stake,
so I must calculate every risk.

490
00:34:52,879 --> 00:34:56,049
By what standard are you calculating
what the pros and cons are?

491
00:34:56,633 --> 00:34:58,719
Marriage isn't about calculations

492
00:34:58,802 --> 00:35:00,345
but a matter of trust
between two people.

493
00:35:00,429 --> 00:35:03,432
Trust alone isn't enough.
You need conviction.

494
00:35:04,766 --> 00:35:07,060
So you're saying
you have no conviction in me.

495
00:35:07,144 --> 00:35:08,270
Hey, Mr. Noh.

496
00:35:08,562 --> 00:35:09,730
It's not that.

497
00:35:10,063 --> 00:35:14,109
I cannot be certain of the effect
marriage will have on my life!

498
00:35:14,192 --> 00:35:16,862
- Ms. Joo.
- How will you build that conviction?

499
00:35:17,112 --> 00:35:19,489
What can I do
to give you that certainty?

500
00:35:34,379 --> 00:35:36,089
Gosh, that was delicious.

501
00:35:36,173 --> 00:35:37,382
I'm so full.

502
00:35:37,466 --> 00:35:38,967
Hey, pull it together, man.

503
00:35:39,051 --> 00:35:41,011
What's for round two?
It's been a while since we've been...

504
00:35:41,094 --> 00:35:43,013
- Thank you for dinner.
- Thank you!

505
00:35:43,096 --> 00:35:44,973
- Thank you.
- Please excuse us first.

506
00:35:45,057 --> 00:35:46,725
Let's call it a night!

507
00:35:46,808 --> 00:35:48,727
- Goodbye.
- I love going to a karaoke room.

508
00:35:48,810 --> 00:35:50,020
- Go now.
- Right?

509
00:35:50,771 --> 00:35:52,272
- Goodbye.
- Bye!

510
00:35:59,363 --> 00:36:00,781
Should I call a cab?

511
00:36:00,864 --> 00:36:03,033
Yes, we should. It's too far to walk.

512
00:36:06,161 --> 00:36:07,996
So you must feel certain about cabs.

513
00:36:23,637 --> 00:36:25,305
Hello, you've reached Joo In-a.

514
00:36:30,185 --> 00:36:31,269
Yes, and?

515
00:37:17,399 --> 00:37:18,734
Thank you for coming.

516
00:37:23,029 --> 00:37:25,741
- Take your time to eat.
- Mr. Noh, one moment.

517
00:37:30,537 --> 00:37:31,788
- Yes?
- Well...

518
00:37:32,372 --> 00:37:33,707
Is she holding the wake
only for one day?

519
00:37:33,790 --> 00:37:35,167
Is she not accepting
any condolence money?

520
00:37:38,503 --> 00:37:40,797
No, she's keeping it simple.

521
00:37:41,631 --> 00:37:43,049
But still, it's too empty.

522
00:37:44,009 --> 00:37:46,011
She told me not to contact
anyone else at work

523
00:37:46,094 --> 00:37:47,679
so we came by ourselves.

524
00:37:48,221 --> 00:37:49,431
But I feel bad.

525
00:37:50,223 --> 00:37:51,975
I heard they had no real contact.

526
00:37:53,018 --> 00:37:54,436
Ms. Joo seems almost too calm.

527
00:37:54,895 --> 00:37:57,230
That's enough. She must have
a lot on her mind.

528
00:37:59,149 --> 00:38:00,317
It's the Vice President.

529
00:38:03,153 --> 00:38:04,196
Hello.

530
00:38:31,640 --> 00:38:33,391
Did you return to Korea for this?

531
00:38:34,559 --> 00:38:36,019
You didn't have to.

532
00:38:36,353 --> 00:38:38,063
I've been living in Seoul recently.

533
00:38:39,189 --> 00:38:41,691
I'm planning to work
on the medical foundation again.

534
00:38:42,484 --> 00:38:43,819
Good for you.

535
00:38:44,778 --> 00:38:45,862
That's a great decision.

536
00:38:48,657 --> 00:38:52,160
I can see that Mr. Noh
is right here for you to lean on.

537
00:38:55,622 --> 00:38:56,665
I mean it.

538
00:38:57,374 --> 00:38:59,459
I'm glad that you have
someone like Mr. Noh Ki-jun...

539
00:39:01,670 --> 00:39:02,671
in your life.

540
00:39:10,387 --> 00:39:11,388
Bye, now.

541
00:39:12,097 --> 00:39:13,098
Bye.

542
00:39:42,711 --> 00:39:45,005
- Are you all right?
- Yes.

543
00:39:45,964 --> 00:39:48,425
The hospital put these together.

544
00:39:49,092 --> 00:39:50,093
They were your father's.

545
00:39:52,512 --> 00:39:53,930
You must be tired.

546
00:39:54,347 --> 00:39:56,433
You should go home now.
You have work tomorrow.

547
00:39:56,516 --> 00:39:57,851
I can do the funeral procession
on my own.

548
00:39:57,934 --> 00:40:00,478
I'll stay.
I already took the day off tomorrow.

549
00:40:00,562 --> 00:40:04,691
- Just go home. I'm fine.
- Come on. I'm really okay.

550
00:40:08,069 --> 00:40:10,196
Your tea's cold.
Let me get you a new one.

551
00:41:11,549 --> 00:41:13,301
What is this, really?

552
00:41:16,596 --> 00:41:18,264
How ridiculous.

553
00:41:23,353 --> 00:41:24,604
I hate him...

554
00:41:27,482 --> 00:41:28,650
yet I pity him.

555
00:41:30,944 --> 00:41:33,071
I pity him, yet I can't forgive him.

556
00:41:35,031 --> 00:41:37,450
I haven't forgiven him,
but he has already passed away.

557
00:41:40,704 --> 00:41:42,038
Seriously.

558
00:41:43,206 --> 00:41:45,917
What do I do?

559
00:41:50,797 --> 00:41:51,881
I can't believe it.

560
00:42:22,162 --> 00:42:24,998
I can just go home and sleep.

561
00:42:25,081 --> 00:42:27,125
You haven't had
anything to eat all day.

562
00:42:27,208 --> 00:42:29,753
I'll only be relieved
after I see you eat something.

563
00:42:30,336 --> 00:42:31,755
What are you going to make me?

564
00:42:32,297 --> 00:42:33,590
Yes, right?

565
00:42:33,673 --> 00:42:34,924
That's true.

566
00:42:35,008 --> 00:42:36,634
- You have a point.
- Yes.

567
00:42:36,885 --> 00:42:37,927
Go on.

568
00:42:38,803 --> 00:42:39,888
Hey.

569
00:42:40,764 --> 00:42:42,098
Hey! Gosh!

570
00:42:42,182 --> 00:42:43,850
Why did you change the passcode?

571
00:42:43,933 --> 00:42:46,144
I got it wrong five times,
so I had to wait five minutes.

572
00:42:46,227 --> 00:42:47,979
- Hello.
- Hello.

573
00:42:48,354 --> 00:42:49,856
- You two were together!
- Right?

574
00:42:49,939 --> 00:42:51,441
- I'm glad.
- Yes.

575
00:42:51,524 --> 00:42:52,859
- Hello.
- Have you all been well?

576
00:42:53,151 --> 00:42:54,277
- Yes.
- Yes.

577
00:42:54,360 --> 00:42:56,112
Why didn't you call me first?

578
00:42:56,196 --> 00:42:59,115
Why did you punch in numbers
recklessly only to complain?

579
00:42:59,491 --> 00:43:01,409
- Why did you change the number?
- Yes, why? How dare you?

580
00:43:01,493 --> 00:43:03,328
- You should've told us first.
- It's my home.

581
00:43:03,411 --> 00:43:04,662
- What's with you?
- Please excuse me.

582
00:43:04,746 --> 00:43:07,040
- No, stay.
- No, come and eat.

583
00:43:07,123 --> 00:43:09,751
- We brought good food.
- Yes.

584
00:43:12,212 --> 00:43:13,588
So what's all this?

585
00:43:20,136 --> 00:43:21,805
We heard the news.

586
00:43:22,055 --> 00:43:24,474
It must've been so shocking.

587
00:43:24,724 --> 00:43:27,936
We wanted to visit you at the wake,
but the funeral was already done.

588
00:43:28,019 --> 00:43:31,189
Ki-jun made a huge scene
and told us not to show up.

589
00:43:31,272 --> 00:43:33,108
We thought you couldn't have eaten
after that shock.

590
00:43:33,191 --> 00:43:34,484
Here's porridge
to help with digestion.

591
00:43:34,734 --> 00:43:35,902
Have some dongchimi with it.

592
00:43:35,985 --> 00:43:40,115
Have some before it gets cold.
I even chopped the liver to make it.

593
00:43:40,698 --> 00:43:43,118
- Eat up.
- Leave it. We'll have it on our own.

594
00:43:43,201 --> 00:43:45,995
What? She has to eat it
while it's hot to enjoy it.

595
00:43:46,079 --> 00:43:47,914
Yes, thank you.

596
00:43:56,548 --> 00:43:58,716
It's delicious.
It's giving me strength.

597
00:43:59,759 --> 00:44:01,219
- I knew it.
- I told you so.

598
00:44:01,302 --> 00:44:03,763
- I should've added wild chives.
- It's good.

599
00:44:03,847 --> 00:44:05,723
- Eat a lot more.
- She's going to get sick!

600
00:44:05,807 --> 00:44:07,767
- Ki-jun, bring water for her meal.
- Yes, hurry.

601
00:44:07,851 --> 00:44:09,185
Come on. Move it.

602
00:44:09,602 --> 00:44:12,564
- It must've been hectic.
- I bet.

603
00:44:12,647 --> 00:44:14,774
I've done a one-day wake
when my grandfather-in-law passed

604
00:44:14,858 --> 00:44:17,402
and it was tighter and more hectic
compared to three-day ones.

605
00:44:17,485 --> 00:44:19,737
Things are more hectic now
than at the wake, okay?

606
00:44:19,821 --> 00:44:22,282
Did Ki-jun actually help out?

607
00:44:22,574 --> 00:44:25,368
I mean, he grew up only with women

608
00:44:25,451 --> 00:44:27,537
I'm not sure
if he can even perform as a man.

609
00:44:27,829 --> 00:44:30,790
Will you try to pick out
proper words when you speak?

610
00:44:31,291 --> 00:44:33,835
- Okay?
- What about my words?

611
00:44:33,918 --> 00:44:35,295
- Eat up.
- Which words?

612
00:44:35,378 --> 00:44:36,504
- Eat.
- "Perform" was kind of odd.

613
00:44:36,588 --> 00:44:37,839
- Performing as a man?
- Performing?

614
00:44:37,922 --> 00:44:39,841
- Performing as a man!
- Hey.

615
00:44:39,924 --> 00:44:41,009
- Hey, man.
- Stop.

616
00:44:41,092 --> 00:44:42,427
You're a big man now.

617
00:44:42,510 --> 00:44:44,637
- There are other words!
- Yes, sure.

618
00:44:44,721 --> 00:44:47,182
Goodness, you're such a man!

619
00:44:47,265 --> 00:44:48,474
A man who can perform.

620
00:44:48,933 --> 00:44:52,270
- Yes, "perform."
- Oh, boy. How adorable.

621
00:44:52,353 --> 00:44:54,731
Hey, that should be enough.
You should go.

622
00:44:54,814 --> 00:44:56,065
Give this to her.

623
00:45:06,284 --> 00:45:07,285
Cab fare.

624
00:45:09,245 --> 00:45:11,372
I can't reimburse anything
before 10 p.m.

625
00:45:11,456 --> 00:45:14,500
There's not much difference.
Just do it.

626
00:45:33,353 --> 00:45:34,771
Let me return the paperwork.

627
00:45:35,772 --> 00:45:38,024
Why hasn't this gone through?

628
00:45:38,107 --> 00:45:40,068
The name on the seal certification
is the previous CEO's.

629
00:45:40,151 --> 00:45:41,819
I'll need one
under the current CEO's name.

630
00:45:42,612 --> 00:45:45,573
Does that mean
I'll need more paperwork?

631
00:45:45,657 --> 00:45:46,824
It's written over there.

632
00:45:49,160 --> 00:45:51,955
Customer number nine,
please come to window four.

633
00:46:06,010 --> 00:46:08,429
If you want a new certification
of the seal impression

634
00:46:08,513 --> 00:46:10,682
you have to go
to a register office, not here.

635
00:46:11,474 --> 00:46:15,228
There, apply for the continued use
of the seal registration card.

636
00:46:15,520 --> 00:46:16,813
Do you have the corporate seal?

637
00:46:17,272 --> 00:46:19,691
You need to take that
to apply for it right away.

638
00:46:20,275 --> 00:46:21,276
Thank you.

639
00:46:22,277 --> 00:46:23,319
Goodbye, then.

640
00:46:36,874 --> 00:46:37,875
Ms. Park.

641
00:46:51,139 --> 00:46:52,265
Where do you work right now?

642
00:46:53,683 --> 00:46:56,352
Why do you ask?

643
00:47:06,154 --> 00:47:07,363
Call me if you'd like to join me.

644
00:47:07,447 --> 00:47:08,906
JEI MEDICAL FOUNDATION
JEON JAE-YEOL

645
00:47:11,284 --> 00:47:12,744
This is a recruitment offer.

646
00:47:16,039 --> 00:47:17,040
Do I...

647
00:47:18,833 --> 00:47:20,710
Do I really deserve this?

648
00:47:24,672 --> 00:47:26,174
I need a talented employee.

649
00:47:27,258 --> 00:47:28,343
That's all.

650
00:47:34,390 --> 00:47:37,060
So this is what I want to emphasize.

651
00:47:37,560 --> 00:47:39,187
When you first joined the company

652
00:47:39,270 --> 00:47:42,690
you were lucky enough
to have me as your direct superior.

653
00:47:42,774 --> 00:47:45,610
Hence, you got the chance
to learn so much from me.

654
00:47:45,693 --> 00:47:48,154
Also, whenever you had
a tough and arduous time...

655
00:47:48,237 --> 00:47:49,697
Cut to the chase, Se-young.

656
00:47:49,947 --> 00:47:51,115
What's your point?

657
00:47:51,199 --> 00:47:53,868
The Audit Team is going to be
separated from the division, right?

658
00:47:54,243 --> 00:47:58,122
So in an effort to give more power
to the Audit Team

659
00:47:58,456 --> 00:48:00,249
we've decided to promote the head.

660
00:48:01,042 --> 00:48:03,503
And you already qualify
more than enough.

661
00:48:06,672 --> 00:48:09,801
I'm saying, you're going to be
a senior managing director.

662
00:48:16,641 --> 00:48:17,642
Thank you.

663
00:48:18,893 --> 00:48:20,019
- Thank you.
- Congratulations!

664
00:48:20,103 --> 00:48:21,270
Congratulations, Ms. Joo.

665
00:48:24,065 --> 00:48:26,651
Now, Senior Managing Director Joo.
Please share a word with us.

666
00:48:28,277 --> 00:48:31,155
I owe it all to you.

667
00:48:31,531 --> 00:48:32,949
I share my deepest gratitude.

668
00:48:33,199 --> 00:48:36,202
Goodness, don't be so humble.

669
00:48:36,285 --> 00:48:39,288
Boo! Be more honest!
That was so boring!

670
00:48:39,372 --> 00:48:41,457
That was so boring.

671
00:48:43,709 --> 00:48:44,710
"Boring"?

672
00:48:50,633 --> 00:48:52,051
Are you looking

673
00:48:53,136 --> 00:48:55,054
to have fun in the office right now?

674
00:48:59,767 --> 00:49:00,810
In that case

675
00:49:01,769 --> 00:49:02,979
how about this?

676
00:49:04,564 --> 00:49:05,565
Like this.

677
00:49:08,359 --> 00:49:09,402
What do you think?

678
00:49:14,699 --> 00:49:15,700
How's that?

679
00:49:18,828 --> 00:49:19,912
Keep it up!

680
00:49:19,996 --> 00:49:22,039
- All right!
- You're the best!

681
00:49:26,836 --> 00:49:29,589
Senior Managing Director Joo,
you don't have to do this.

682
00:49:30,381 --> 00:49:32,300
I don't think
I'll be able to check on it often.

683
00:49:32,383 --> 00:49:33,926
I'm getting my own office.

684
00:49:34,594 --> 00:49:37,013
Wow, your very own office.

685
00:49:37,472 --> 00:49:40,349
- That's awesome.
- Hey, are you free tonight?

686
00:49:40,766 --> 00:49:41,893
My treat.

687
00:49:42,435 --> 00:49:44,479
Or do you want to come to my place?

688
00:49:44,562 --> 00:49:46,606
I think I can recreate
the pasta we had last time

689
00:49:46,689 --> 00:49:48,191
so I bought a lot of ingredients.

690
00:49:48,274 --> 00:49:51,277
Gosh, the senior managing director
even knows how to cook?

691
00:49:54,322 --> 00:49:55,573
But what a shame.

692
00:49:55,656 --> 00:49:56,782
I have to go to my mom's place.

693
00:49:56,866 --> 00:49:59,368
They're making a big batch of kimchi,
so I have to go and help.

694
00:49:59,452 --> 00:50:00,495
Is that so?

695
00:50:00,912 --> 00:50:03,623
I can't help it, then.
Go and help them out, okay?

696
00:50:04,540 --> 00:50:05,833
- What?
- Where are you going?

697
00:50:05,917 --> 00:50:06,959
To the office.

698
00:50:08,544 --> 00:50:11,380
- We're at work. Hands off.
- No one is around. No one's here.

699
00:50:12,340 --> 00:50:14,509
- You aren't mad, are you?
- I am.

700
00:50:15,301 --> 00:50:18,471
Ki-jun, you'll find
more napa cabbage outside.

701
00:50:18,554 --> 00:50:19,555
Bring them in.

702
00:50:20,515 --> 00:50:21,807
- Hurry up.
- Wait.

703
00:50:22,558 --> 00:50:23,935
Are you trying to give away
free kimchi?

704
00:50:24,477 --> 00:50:26,020
Why are you making so much kimchi?

705
00:50:26,270 --> 00:50:28,022
The kids don't eat
a lot of kimchi anyway.

706
00:50:28,272 --> 00:50:30,149
We have
another family member this year.

707
00:50:30,233 --> 00:50:32,652
What? Another family member? Who?

708
00:50:33,194 --> 00:50:35,321
Mom, it hasn't happened yet.

709
00:50:35,404 --> 00:50:38,616
What? What are you talking about?
Why is our family getting bigger?

710
00:50:38,699 --> 00:50:40,993
We're talking about your Ms. Joo.

711
00:50:42,119 --> 00:50:43,538
It's her.

712
00:50:43,621 --> 00:50:45,414
She's practically family now.

713
00:50:45,706 --> 00:50:47,750
- Goodness.
- While we're at it

714
00:50:47,833 --> 00:50:49,794
do you have any specific plans?

715
00:50:49,877 --> 00:50:51,796
It's not easy to secure a good date
for a nice venue.

716
00:50:51,879 --> 00:50:54,465
Why is everyone jumping so far ahead?

717
00:50:54,549 --> 00:50:55,591
Also...

718
00:50:56,008 --> 00:50:57,969
she'll be really busy for a while.

719
00:50:58,803 --> 00:50:59,804
- Why?
- Why?

720
00:51:05,351 --> 00:51:07,478
She got promoted
to senior managing director.

721
00:51:08,062 --> 00:51:10,523
Do you know how busy they are
at a major company like ours?

722
00:51:10,773 --> 00:51:12,441
That's who In-a is.

723
00:51:12,525 --> 00:51:14,277
She's a woman of great caliber.

724
00:51:14,360 --> 00:51:16,904
How dare you try to lock up
a great person like her

725
00:51:16,988 --> 00:51:19,407
as the daughter-in-law
of a nameless family like ours? Gosh.

726
00:51:19,490 --> 00:51:22,618
Good grief.
What a great boyfriend you are.

727
00:51:23,160 --> 00:51:25,037
But that's really amazing.

728
00:51:25,329 --> 00:51:28,165
Wait, a senior managing director
is right below the vice president.

729
00:51:28,249 --> 00:51:29,792
That's not a job for just anyone.

730
00:51:29,875 --> 00:51:32,336
Of course not.
My In-a isn't just anyone.

731
00:51:32,837 --> 00:51:34,463
I guess she'll be busy.

732
00:51:35,047 --> 00:51:37,383
The least I can do
is not stand in her way

733
00:51:37,592 --> 00:51:39,927
if I can't be of help to her
who is about to do great work.

734
00:51:40,011 --> 00:51:43,180
They'll figure it out on their own
in good time.

735
00:51:43,264 --> 00:51:46,809
We'll figure it out on our own
so don't worry too much, okay?

736
00:52:22,094 --> 00:52:23,179
It's good.

737
00:52:58,673 --> 00:52:59,715
In-a!

738
00:53:01,342 --> 00:53:03,094
Hey, what's going on? What is it?

739
00:53:03,427 --> 00:53:05,096
- Is something going on?
- What's this apron?

740
00:53:06,722 --> 00:53:07,723
Oh, this.

741
00:53:08,391 --> 00:53:10,768
I had to run out
in the middle of making kimchi.

742
00:53:11,310 --> 00:53:15,106
I mean, you've never called me out
so suddenly like this.

743
00:53:15,189 --> 00:53:16,649
I have something to say, Ki-jun.

744
00:53:18,818 --> 00:53:19,819
What is it?

745
00:53:25,866 --> 00:53:26,867
Well...

746
00:53:28,327 --> 00:53:29,954
It'll be like it always was

747
00:53:30,746 --> 00:53:32,039
but I'll be even busier from now on.

748
00:53:33,040 --> 00:53:35,042
I'll have to get to work early,
work overtime often

749
00:53:35,126 --> 00:53:36,502
and have to work
outside the office, too.

750
00:53:37,503 --> 00:53:40,297
I won't be able to text
or call back as I do now.

751
00:53:41,549 --> 00:53:42,883
And above all...

752
00:53:44,760 --> 00:53:45,970
I think...

753
00:53:47,430 --> 00:53:48,472
my personality may become

754
00:53:49,640 --> 00:53:51,434
even worse than what it is now.

755
00:53:52,435 --> 00:53:54,770
My new position comes with that much
responsibility and pressure.

756
00:53:55,813 --> 00:54:01,110
I might become much pickier,
more impatient and easily angered

757
00:54:01,193 --> 00:54:02,737
and even try
to vent my stress on you.

758
00:54:06,991 --> 00:54:08,033
And?

759
00:54:10,369 --> 00:54:11,746
What are you trying to say?

760
00:54:18,878 --> 00:54:20,129
Do you want to live with me?

761
00:54:22,882 --> 00:54:24,633
Let's try living together.

762
00:54:27,803 --> 00:54:29,972
- Are you asking me to move in?
- Yes.

763
00:54:36,312 --> 00:54:38,063
Why did you suddenly get this idea?

764
00:54:39,732 --> 00:54:40,816
Today

765
00:54:42,109 --> 00:54:43,694
I was thrilled to hear the news.

766
00:54:44,695 --> 00:54:47,198
Then you were the first person
I wanted to share it with.

767
00:54:48,115 --> 00:54:50,659
I celebrated alone at home,
but it wasn't that fun.

768
00:54:51,076 --> 00:54:53,454
And the pasta wasn't as good
as the time we had it together.

769
00:54:54,538 --> 00:54:55,790
At some point

770
00:54:56,290 --> 00:54:59,335
I must've gotten used to sharing
my joy and sadness with you.

771
00:55:02,046 --> 00:55:03,339
But I never realized it.

772
00:55:04,340 --> 00:55:07,593
I was already imagining
my everyday life with you

773
00:55:07,885 --> 00:55:08,886
but I...

774
00:55:09,386 --> 00:55:14,141
I just got tied up by the idea
that I shouldn't get married.

775
00:55:17,061 --> 00:55:18,103
Honestly

776
00:55:19,355 --> 00:55:22,191
I'm not sure
if I can deal with marriage.

777
00:55:23,609 --> 00:55:26,070
My father
could not keep his family together

778
00:55:26,153 --> 00:55:28,614
and my mom never became a part
of the thing called marriage.

779
00:55:29,365 --> 00:55:30,449
It's a concept

780
00:55:31,784 --> 00:55:33,869
that never existed in my life

781
00:55:35,120 --> 00:55:36,413
so it's true that I feel uncertain.

782
00:55:38,207 --> 00:55:39,250
But despite that

783
00:55:40,584 --> 00:55:42,419
I want to be with you, Ki-jun.

784
00:55:43,879 --> 00:55:45,798
So I want to take my time

785
00:55:47,007 --> 00:55:50,427
and start by living together.

786
00:56:06,861 --> 00:56:09,113
What's going on?
You have to tell me yes or no.

787
00:56:09,196 --> 00:56:11,574
I'm rambling on all by myself,
and I'm starting to feel embarrassed.

788
00:56:15,828 --> 00:56:16,829
How much worse...

789
00:56:18,747 --> 00:56:20,291
will your personality become?

790
00:56:23,210 --> 00:56:24,336
A little bit.

791
00:56:29,842 --> 00:56:31,927
Okay, let's stay together

792
00:56:32,636 --> 00:56:33,637
no matter what that life is.

793
00:56:57,912 --> 00:56:58,954
Wait.

794
00:56:59,538 --> 00:57:01,123
- Why?
- Gosh, you smell.

795
00:57:31,862 --> 00:57:35,324
Just like that,
our secret private life began.

796
00:57:40,537 --> 00:57:43,415
It was filled with ordinary
yet precious everyday moments.

797
00:57:47,836 --> 00:57:49,588
Gold bars!

798
00:57:50,005 --> 00:57:51,090
Hey.

799
00:57:51,632 --> 00:57:53,008
Merry Christmas.

800
00:57:54,760 --> 00:57:57,262
And there were moments
that shimmered like a dream.

801
00:58:12,236 --> 00:58:14,196
But there were dark sides
that were better off not known...

802
00:58:14,738 --> 00:58:15,906
Gosh, it's so hot.

803
00:58:22,454 --> 00:58:23,539
Why is it so cold?

804
00:58:26,417 --> 00:58:27,584
So cold.

805
00:58:28,669 --> 00:58:29,753
Gosh, it's chilly.

806
00:58:29,962 --> 00:58:31,088
So hot.

807
00:58:33,007 --> 00:58:34,008
Wait, what?

808
00:58:35,384 --> 00:58:37,136
Hey, the temperature.

809
00:58:37,553 --> 00:58:39,430
Oh, come on. Why does it keep...

810
00:58:39,513 --> 00:58:41,724
Why is this house so cold?

811
00:58:43,183 --> 00:58:45,352
See? This is why it's so cold.

812
00:58:45,602 --> 00:58:47,438
...and unexpected
temperature differences.

813
00:58:48,313 --> 00:58:49,481
Wait, hey.

814
00:58:52,609 --> 00:58:55,821
I told you to leave the bathroom door
wide open over and over again.

815
00:58:55,904 --> 00:58:58,073
- It gets damp.
- It's winter, not summer.

816
00:58:58,157 --> 00:59:00,909
And I hate smelling the drain
in the living room when it's open!

817
00:59:00,993 --> 00:59:02,786
Are you going to clean it up
when it develops mold?

818
00:59:02,870 --> 00:59:04,455
Yes! When did I not do it?

819
00:59:05,706 --> 00:59:07,082
The most critical thing was this.

820
00:59:11,837 --> 00:59:13,714
The biggest difficulty between us

821
00:59:14,173 --> 00:59:15,424
was that we also shared
our work life.

822
00:59:15,507 --> 00:59:17,176
SENIOR MANAGING DIRECTOR JOO IN-A

823
00:59:17,301 --> 00:59:18,677
For the official schedule tomorrow

824
00:59:18,761 --> 00:59:21,055
you can just attend the event
before the actual ceremony.

825
00:59:22,681 --> 00:59:26,101
You seem upset.
Is there a problem with the schedule?

826
00:59:26,185 --> 00:59:27,936
No, it's not that.

827
00:59:29,813 --> 00:59:31,190
I shouldn't be like this.

828
00:59:32,232 --> 00:59:35,402
Ms. Ahn, are you aware
of the hungry judge effect?

829
00:59:35,944 --> 00:59:37,654
- Sorry?
- It's a study that says

830
00:59:37,738 --> 00:59:40,199
judges tend to give strict rulings
before their breaks

831
00:59:40,282 --> 00:59:44,203
and more tolerant ones
after they come back from lunch.

832
00:59:44,912 --> 00:59:48,832
It means
something seemingly petty like hunger

833
00:59:49,666 --> 00:59:51,877
can affect your work.

834
00:59:53,462 --> 00:59:54,963
Ms. Joo, are you hungry?

835
00:59:55,380 --> 00:59:56,507
No, it's not that.

836
00:59:56,924 --> 00:59:59,968
It's just that hard to differentiate
between work and private life.

837
01:00:00,260 --> 01:00:02,221
If you are,
I can prepare something...

838
01:00:02,304 --> 01:00:04,056
Oh, not at all.

839
01:00:04,348 --> 01:00:06,183
- Please continue.
- Yes.

840
01:00:06,642 --> 01:00:08,185
- So before the ceremony...
- That's true.

841
01:00:08,310 --> 01:00:11,605
Drawing the line
between work and personal life

842
01:00:11,688 --> 01:00:13,649
is never as simple as it sounds.

843
01:00:13,732 --> 01:00:14,983
Da-young, one iced Americano, please.

844
01:00:15,067 --> 01:00:16,735
Add another shot
and fill it up with ice.

845
01:00:17,778 --> 01:00:19,363
Yes, okay.

846
01:00:19,446 --> 01:00:21,073
Oh, come on.

847
01:00:22,991 --> 01:00:24,827
- Here it is.
- Yes, thank you.

848
01:00:25,994 --> 01:00:27,579
- Hey.
- My gosh.

849
01:00:28,122 --> 01:00:29,540
Did you get into a fight with her?

850
01:00:32,918 --> 01:00:34,211
You know what?

851
01:00:35,170 --> 01:00:37,422
I still can't get used
to you working here.

852
01:00:40,425 --> 01:00:41,802
Is it that obvious?

853
01:00:41,885 --> 01:00:43,178
Totally obvious.

854
01:00:43,262 --> 01:00:45,389
Smile a little.
You're practically broadcasting it.

855
01:00:47,224 --> 01:00:48,225
Okay.

856
01:00:51,103 --> 01:00:52,104
Hey, there.

857
01:01:11,415 --> 01:01:12,958
Gosh. Seriously.

858
01:01:23,010 --> 01:01:24,386
I was a little too harsh...

859
01:01:28,473 --> 01:01:30,726
I'm sorry.
It wasn't even a big deal...

860
01:01:32,352 --> 01:01:33,979
No, why should I apologize first?

861
01:01:34,771 --> 01:01:36,648
Yes, I was wrong.

862
01:01:37,107 --> 01:01:38,192
I don't want to do it.

863
01:01:39,693 --> 01:01:40,736
Jeez.

864
01:01:41,486 --> 01:01:42,529
Did they get into a fight?

865
01:01:43,071 --> 01:01:44,323
Should I just say it first?

866
01:01:45,073 --> 01:01:46,700
Yes, I'll say it first.

867
01:01:46,783 --> 01:01:50,871
We clash with personal emotions
countless times a day at work.

868
01:01:51,914 --> 01:01:52,998
Darn it.

869
01:02:04,259 --> 01:02:06,220
And those feelings affect our work.

870
01:02:09,806 --> 01:02:10,933
JEI MEDICAL FOUNDATION
JEON JAE-YEOL

871
01:02:11,016 --> 01:02:12,142
And because of work

872
01:02:12,768 --> 01:02:14,561
your feelings falter once again.

873
01:02:25,322 --> 01:02:28,533
Perhaps separating
work and private life

874
01:02:29,076 --> 01:02:30,744
isn't about drawing a hard line

875
01:02:31,370 --> 01:02:34,748
but constantly trying
to keep the balance.

876
01:02:41,004 --> 01:02:42,214
Manager Noh.

877
01:02:42,297 --> 01:02:45,133
The first diagram in the report
needs to be revised.

878
01:02:47,511 --> 01:02:48,804
Yes, Ms. Joo.

879
01:02:49,721 --> 01:02:50,889
Excuse me.

880
01:02:50,973 --> 01:02:51,974
He used it!

881
01:02:52,266 --> 01:02:53,392
Director Hwang

882
01:02:53,475 --> 01:02:55,602
used his corporate card again
at a hotel on a business trip!

883
01:02:55,686 --> 01:02:57,688
Get there now.
You need to catch him red-handed.

884
01:02:57,771 --> 01:02:58,855
Oh, no.

885
01:02:58,939 --> 01:03:00,983
Everyone except for Mr. Noh
has work out of the office

886
01:03:01,066 --> 01:03:02,276
so we have no other people.

887
01:03:22,296 --> 01:03:23,297
Leaving so soon?

888
01:03:29,219 --> 01:03:30,804
The ice has melted just enough

889
01:03:31,054 --> 01:03:32,764
so the aroma should be
at its best now.

890
01:03:33,765 --> 01:03:34,808
Feels like a shame to leave it.

891
01:03:38,562 --> 01:03:39,730
You can have it.

892
01:03:50,991 --> 01:03:52,075
She just left.

893
01:04:03,337 --> 01:04:04,629
His side has entered, too.

894
01:05:22,165 --> 01:05:24,709
Hello, we're from the Audit Team.

895
01:05:25,293 --> 01:05:26,378
Director Hwang.

896
01:05:26,461 --> 01:05:28,505
I don't think
your corporate card covers

897
01:05:29,339 --> 01:05:31,216
your date expenses.

898
01:05:36,263 --> 01:05:38,515
It's always much more fun
to do the field work.

899
01:05:38,682 --> 01:05:40,559
We had great teamwork today, Ms. Joo.

900
01:05:40,642 --> 01:05:41,810
Yes.

901
01:05:42,352 --> 01:05:44,479
We're done with work, so give it now.

902
01:05:48,608 --> 01:05:50,277
I'm hungry. Do you want to go eat?

903
01:05:50,527 --> 01:05:52,320
It's chilly,
so how about pork backbone stew?

904
01:05:52,404 --> 01:05:53,780
We'll have it sizzling hot.

905
01:05:53,864 --> 01:05:56,199
We're here at a hotel, so let's go
to a fine dining restaurant.

906
01:06:03,123 --> 01:06:04,666
That's not funny. What is that?

907
01:06:04,749 --> 01:06:06,918
Don't even. You just smiled.

908
01:06:07,002 --> 01:06:08,295
You did. Look.

909
01:06:08,378 --> 01:06:10,464
- You smiled.
- Yes, because my boss told a joke.

910
01:06:10,547 --> 01:06:12,632
Whatever. I know you found it funny.

911
01:06:13,550 --> 01:06:16,011
- Let's eat the backbone stew.
- That sounds great.

912
01:06:16,094 --> 01:06:19,639
- And I'm sorry.
- For what?

913
01:06:20,015 --> 01:06:21,099
This morning.

914
01:06:23,185 --> 01:06:25,645
Yes, I felt bad, too.
I lashed out at you.

915
01:06:26,563 --> 01:06:30,400
- Let's not fight, okay?
- Yes, let's not fight anymore.

916
01:06:37,324 --> 01:06:38,617
Let's go.

917
01:06:42,078 --> 01:06:43,205
I love stew.

918
01:06:55,592 --> 01:06:58,470
FILING FOR LOVE

919
01:06:58,553 --> 01:06:59,763
Here we go.

920
01:07:00,013 --> 01:07:02,766
GUEST APPEARANCE BY JANG HYUK-JIN

921
01:07:03,683 --> 01:07:05,227
Can you follow that car?

922
01:07:05,310 --> 01:07:06,728
One second.

923
01:07:07,437 --> 01:07:08,939
Don't get so close to James...

924
01:07:14,402 --> 01:07:16,488
You can't look disheveled
in front of your head.

925
01:07:18,365 --> 01:07:21,952
You can't look disheveled in front...
Sorry.

926
01:07:23,954 --> 01:07:24,996
Cut!

927
01:07:25,497 --> 01:07:26,540
Wait.

928
01:07:27,791 --> 01:07:29,167
He snapped it.

929
01:07:29,960 --> 01:07:31,044
I caught it.

930
01:07:33,380 --> 01:07:35,549
WAIT, I WASN'T SUPPOSED TO GET IT

931
01:07:38,426 --> 01:07:39,636
Mission success!

932
01:07:42,639 --> 01:07:44,641
Why is this so easy to win?

933
01:07:45,976 --> 01:07:47,060
My gosh.

934
01:07:57,112 --> 01:07:58,196
Don't overreact.

935
01:07:58,655 --> 01:08:00,865
Don't worry about Mr. Ahn.

936
01:08:01,074 --> 01:08:02,367
I'm sorry, I'll go again.

937
01:08:05,829 --> 01:08:08,331
Salt? No, we need to do it over.

938
01:08:11,376 --> 01:08:13,461
Do something!
You can't just leave him here...

939
01:08:13,837 --> 01:08:15,797
I'm sorry. One more time.

940
01:08:15,880 --> 01:08:17,382
I'll do it better!

941
01:08:17,465 --> 01:08:19,467
Signing of the sale agreement...
What am I saying?

942
01:08:21,136 --> 01:08:22,721
"Signing of the sale agreement."

943
01:08:23,346 --> 01:08:25,974
Tomorrow, major subsidiaries
will be signed and sold off.

944
01:08:26,933 --> 01:08:28,184
The signing of the sale agreement...

945
01:08:32,897 --> 01:08:35,317
It's like, "We're here already,
so why don't we just kiss?"

946
01:08:35,400 --> 01:08:37,027
"Should we go there?"

947
01:08:37,736 --> 01:08:39,362
Wait, why are you laughing?

948
01:08:39,446 --> 01:08:41,865
- What? It's funny!
- Why did you laugh?

949
01:08:41,948 --> 01:08:43,199
He just wanted a meal with you.

950
01:08:46,119 --> 01:08:47,287
Why is this so hot?

951
01:08:47,370 --> 01:08:49,080
- Yes, it's really hot.
- It's so hot!

952
01:09:39,089 --> 01:09:41,091
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn
and Jennifer Lim

